tip.text: Coffee tonic and creme brûlée is a solid choice, head round the corner for a cool hipster street (I enjoyed the magazine shop)
The place for rice sticks "tteok-bokki" with ramen! Super popular so come at off peak times.
A sunglasses shop may be an unusual recommendation but come here for some really quirky interior design. Worth a wander!
A beautiful hanok teahouse with stunning views. This tea room has expanded across Seoul but this branch is slightly less frantic due to its location. Order the signature sweet pumpkin rice cake
Famed for experimental beers, come see this outpost in Seoul of the award-winning Copenhagen-based brewer Mikkeller.  An abundance of small-batch time limited beverages, their stout game is strong!
Delicious Taco's, shells freshly made so eat quickly whilst hot, Veg Quesadilla a little too cheesy for some tastes but recommend everything on the menu!

Getting bored of the fantasy of the speakeasy. Come for a solid, well-made drink. The environment is about the people (not secret entrances & suspenders), Serving food that matches up to the bourbons.

tip.text: Great concept, spirits and ingredients sourced entirely from the region. Owner Vijay Mudaliar’s mission isn’t going to be easy, but I think Native will be part of growing tide for Asian craft spirits.

A lowly Cantonese cafe may not be the first place that comes to mind when dreaming of a cave full of gold, but this bingshi in Guangzhou hides treasures of the liquid variety - Earl Grey Dark & Stormy
A promotion of Indonesian culture and exacting attention to detail, look out for locally made ceramic cups, island ingredients and an absolutely unique infused arak program.
Post-speakeasy, post-KTV, post-truth. You could study Nick Haas’s Skinny’s as an ironic 2016 re-boot of the popular Singapore pub KTV. Or you could just head there for a beer and a shot.

Queen’s strong suit is in agave spirits, and she hopes to endear the gin-driven city to mezcal and tequila with cocktails like Chilli Paste Yo Face that mixes tequila with ginger and a kick of chilli.
Pulled into this venue by Jiang Yifu's Congee recipe posted in Drink Magazine (see link) - worth checking if the venue is open before venturing there but looks like good drinks are in available
The minds of Jazz Club Heyday got loose with their new supperclub. The live band are front and centre at this one-stop shop of dinner, drinks and dancing, that is all about funk and sweet soul music.

tip.text: Alice, in the Gangnam area of South Korea’s capital, is a plush bar – discreetly hidden behind a flower shop – that draws on the multi-sensory experience.
I'm still craving their ricotta cheese salad (not healthy 😂) and panini a year on! A must stop but go hungry!
